A special council meeting to consider a motion of no confidence against Cape Town Executive Mayor Patricia de Lille will take place on 15 February. City of Cape Town speaker Dirk Smit reportedly said that he has received a motion of no confidence to remove de Lille from office. “I have also received a request from 118 councilors to convene an urgent council meeting to consider the motion,” Smit said. Smit has asked councilors to reschedule their diaries for the meeting. -TNA Reporter